---
title: Radio Buttons
---

p.-text
  | In order to use a radio button just use an <code>input type="radio"</code> with the class <code>a-input</code>.
  | Also, in order to have the checkbox properly styled, you must add an empty label for the checkbox immediately after
  | it's declaration. More labels can be added next to it.

.-mb4.-mt2
  div(style="display:flex; align-items: center")
    input(type="radio", class="a-input", name="example", id="radio01", checked)
    label(for="radio01")

    label.-text.-ml1(for="radio01") Radio 1

  div(style="display:flex; align-items: center")
    input(type="radio", class="a-input", name="example", id="radio02")
    label(for="radio02")

    label.-text.-ml1(for="radio02") Radio 2

  div(style="display:flex; align-items: center")
    input(type="radio", class="a-input", name="example", id="radio03")
    label(for="radio03")

    label.-text.-ml1(for="radio03") Radio 3

  :code(lang="html")
    <input type="checkbox" class="a-input" name="example" id="radio01" checked>
    <label for="radio01"></label>
    <label class="c-text -ml1" for="radio01">Radio 1</label>

    <input type="checkbox" class="a-input" name="example" id="radio02">
    <label for="radio02"></label>
    <label class="c-text -ml1" for="radio02">Radio 2</label>

    <input type="checkbox" class="a-input" name="example" id="radio03">
    <label for="radio03"></label>
    <label class="c-text -ml1" for="radio03">Radio 3</label>
